Pasta e Ceci
  --America's Test Kitchen

2 oz pancetta, cut into 1/2" pieces
1 small carrot, peeled and cut into 1/2" pieces
1 small celery rib cut into 1/2" pieces
4 garlic cloves, peeled
1 onion, halved and cut into 1" pieces
14 oz can whole peeled tomatoes, drained
1/4 c evoo + exxtra for serving
1 anchovy fillet, rinsed, patted dry, and minced
1/4 tsp red pepper flakes
2 tsp minced fresh rosemary
2x15 oz cans chickpeas (do not drain)
2 c water
salt and pepper
8 oz (1 1/2 c) ditalini
1 tbsp lemon juice
1 tbsp minced fresh parsley
1 oz (1/c) grated parmesan

Process pancetta in food processor until ground to paste, ~30 s, scraping down sides of bowl as needed. Add carrot, celery, and garlic and pulse until finely chopped, 8-10 pulses. Transfer mixture to large dutch oven. Pulse tomatoes in now empty food processor until coarsely chopped, 8-10 pulses; set aside. Add oil to pancetta mixture in dutch oven and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until fond begins to form on bottom of pot, ~5 min Add anchovy, pepper flakes, and rosemary and cook until fragrant, ~1 min. Stir in tomatoes, chickpeas and their liquid, water, and 1 tsp salt and bring to boil, scraping up any browned bits. Reduce heat to medium low and simmer for 10 min. Add pasta and cook, stirring frequently, until tender, 10-12 min. Stir in lemon juice and parsley and season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve, passing parmesan and extra oil separately.


Notes: another short pasta like orzo can be substituted, but use weight not volume
